<h2>Consolidated Detailed Test Cases</h2>

<!-- For each test case include name, description, preconditions, and detailed step-by-step execution -->

<h3>TS-001 — Basic cross-subdomain login persistence (Happy path)</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Verify that after logging in on the main domain, the user remains authenticated when navigating to other subdomains under the same parent domain.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Test account exists; browser cache & cookies cleared; environment accessible via HTTPS; cookie `Domain` configured to `.pgl.co.uk`.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Open a fresh browser session (no cookies/cache).</li>
<li>Navigate to https://www.pgl.co.uk/login.</li>
<li>Enter valid test credentials and complete login.</li>
<li>Confirm successful login by observing user name/profile link on www.pgl.co.uk.</li>
<li>In same browser session, navigate to https://holiday.pgl.co.uk (or another subdomain).</li>
<li>Confirm the user is shown as authenticated (profile visible, access to protected pages without login prompt).</li>
<li>Open browser dev tools → Application → Cookies and verify that session cookie `Domain` is `.pgl.co.uk` and is present.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> User remains authenticated across the subdomain; session cookie is set with parent domain and transmitted to subdomain requests.</p>

<h3>TS-002 — Login then redirect to subdomain</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Validate that a post-auth redirect to a different subdomain retains the authenticated session.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Redirect configured; same preconditions as TS-001.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Open a fresh browser session.</li>
<li>Navigate to https://www.pgl.co.uk/login and perform login with valid credentials.</li>
<li>Trigger an action that redirects the user post-login to https://services.pgl.co.uk/dashboard (or equivalent).</li>
<li>After redirect, confirm the dashboard loads and displays user-specific data without requiring another login.</li>
<li>Check cookies to ensure session cookie exists with `Domain=.pgl.co.uk`.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Redirected subdomain shows authenticated session and no additional login is required.</p>

<h3>TS-003 — Cookie Secure flag and HTTP vs HTTPS</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Ensure cookies that have `Secure` flag aren't sent over HTTP and that authentication only works over HTTPS.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Cookie configured with Secure; both HTTP and HTTPS endpoints available for testing.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Using a fresh browser, log in over HTTPS to https://www.pgl.co.uk.</li>
<li>Confirm authentication on an HTTPS subdomain (https://holiday.pgl.co.uk).</li>
<li>Navigate to http://holiday.pgl.co.uk (HTTP). Observe whether user is authenticated.</li>
<li>Inspect cookies on HTTP and HTTPS contexts to see if `Secure` cookie is present in requests.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Secure cookie is only sent over HTTPS; HTTP pages do not receive the cookie and therefore show unauthenticated state.</p>

<h3>TS-004 — Cookie Domain attribute correctness</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Verify that setting cookie `Domain` to `.pgl.co.uk` makes it available to all subdomains, while setting it to a specific subdomain limits its scope.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Ability to configure cookie Domain or test environments with different domain settings.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Configure cookie to `Domain=.pgl.co.uk` (if environment allows) and restart app if needed.</li>
<li>Log in and confirm cookie `Domain` attribute via dev tools.</li>
<li>Navigate across multiple subdomains to confirm authentication.</li>
<li>Repeat with cookie set to `Domain=www.pgl.co.uk` and verify other subdomains do not receive the cookie.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Parent-domain cookie is visible to all subdomains; explicit subdomain cookie is not.</p>

<h3>TS-005 — SameSite attribute: None vs Lax vs Strict</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Test cookies with different SameSite settings to observe cross-site behavior (especially for iframe or cross-origin redirects).</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Ability to configure SameSite values and test pages that simulate cross-site contexts.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Set SameSite=None and Secure=true; log in and attempt cross-site/iframe scenarios that rely on cookies.</li>
<li>Observe whether session cookie is used in embedded or cross-site requests.</li>
<li>Change SameSite to Lax, repeat the scenario, and note differences.</li>
<li>Change SameSite to Strict and repeat.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> SameSite=None allows cross-site contexts when Secure=true; Lax/Strict limit cookie usage in cross-site flows per spec.</p>

<h3>TS-006 — Logout propagation across subdomains</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Confirm that logging out from one subdomain invalidates session on other subdomains.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> User logged in and authenticated on at least two subdomains.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Log in on https://www.pgl.co.uk.</li>
<li>Open https://holiday.pgl.co.uk in a new tab and confirm authenticated state.</li>
<li>On one tab, perform logout action (click logout, server-side invalidate session).</li>
<li>On the other tab, refresh protected pages and confirm the user is logged out.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Session invalidation is propagated and user is logged out across subdomains.</p>

<h3>TS-007 — Session expiry and cookie expiry boundary</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Verify behaviour when session timeout occurs and align cookie expiry boundaries.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Testable short session timeout (configurable) or ability to manipulate session storage.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Log in and confirm authenticated state across subdomains.</li>
<li>Wait for configured session timeout (e.g., 1 minute) plus a small buffer.</li>
<li>Attempt to access a protected resource on a subdomain.</li>
<li>Confirm user is prompted to re-authenticate.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> After expiry, session is invalidated and protected pages require login on all subdomains.</p>

<h3>TS-008 — Concurrent sessions and session fixation</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Test that session cookies can't be trivially replayed/reused from other clients and that server-side protections exist.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Two separate browser contexts (or ability to set cookies manually).</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Log in on Browser A and extract session cookie value.</li>
<li>In Browser B (or private window), import or set the same cookie value for parent domain.</li>
<li>Attempt to access protected resources.</li>
<li>Observe whether server accepts the cookie or forces re-authentication / denies access.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Server rejects cookie reuse, rotates session identifiers on login, and prevents fixation attacks.</p>

<h3>TS-009 — Cookie header size and server/proxy limits</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Confirm behavior when cookie headers approach or exceed typical HTTP header size limits.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Ability to create large cookies; knowledge of proxy limits.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Create a large session cookie and log in.</li>
<li>Perform requests that include cookie headers to subdomains.</li>
<li>Observe for truncated cookies, HTTP 400/431 responses, or other errors from proxies/servers.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Requests fail or cookies truncated if header limits exceeded; document failure mode and remediation.</p>

<h3>TS-010 — Subdomain permutations (www, regional, localized)</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Validate session across typical subdomain patterns used in production including locale-specific and service-specific subdomains.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Multiple subdomains configured and reachable.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Log in on primary domain.</li>
<li>Visit a list of subdomains (e.g., en.pgl.co.uk, fr.pgl.co.uk, holiday.pgl.co.uk, services.pgl.co.uk).</li>
<li>Verify authenticated state and access to protected resources on each.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Authentication persists across all subdomains covered by cookie domain.</p>

<h3>TS-011 — Different port behavior</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Check cookie behavior when the same host is accessed on different ports.</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Service available on alternate port(s) for testing.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Log in on https://www.pgl.co.uk (default port 443).</li>
<li>Access same hostname on alternate port (https://www.pgl.co.uk:8443 if available).</li>
<li>Verify if cookie is sent and whether authentication persists.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Browser sends cookie to same host/scheme regardless of port; verify server behavior. Note any infrastructure that isolates by port.</p>

<h3>TS-012 — Browser privacy features and third-party cookie blocking</h3>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> Ensure application handles browsers that block third-party cookies or implement Intelligent Tracking Prevention (ITP).</p>
<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Browsers with strict tracking prevention (Safari, Brave, Firefox strict) available for testing.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Open a privacy-focused browser or enable strict tracking protection.</li>
<li>Log in on primary domain then perform flows that rely on cookie sharing (cross-origin iframe or resource requests).</li>
<li>Observe whether session persists and whether the app provides fallback or prompts.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Some browsers may block cookies in specific contexts; document behavior and recommend mitigations (e.g., SameSite=None+Secure, server-side token exchange).</p>

<hr>
<p><em>Notes & test data references:</em></p>
<ul>
<li>Use dedicated test accounts with known credentials (e.g., testuser+ts01@pgl.co.uk / Password1!).</li>
<li>Where environment config changes required (cookie Domain, SameSite), coordinate with dev/ops to perform controlled toggles or use staging environments.</li>
<li>For negative tests (cookie reuse, large cookies), use dev tools, cookie editors, or proxy tools (Burp, Fiddler) to manipulate cookies and headers.</li>
<li>Record results and capture HTTP(S) request/response headers and screenshots for any failures.</li>
</ul>

